  <section id="why" class="lr-sec w-section lr-why--photo" data-nav-surface="dark">
    <div class="lr-why__scrim" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="w-container">
      <div class="w-reveal lr-measure">
        <span class="lr-eyebrow"><svg class="w-icon"><use href="#i-trending"/></svg>Why trust became the thing buyers buy on</span>
        <h2 class="lr-h2" style="margin-top:16px">When everyone can sound perfect, a peer is the only proof left.</h2>
        <p class="lr-body">A sharp pitch used to be a real signal — writing one well took effort, so buyers read polish as competence. Generative AI broke that link: flawless copy now costs almost nothing, and every channel sounds equally sure of itself. So buyers lean on the one voice with <strong>nothing to gain</strong> — another customer who's already done the exact thing they're weighing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lr-stats w-stagger">
        <div class="lr-stat w-reveal w-reveal--scale"><div class="lr-stat__n">66%</div><div class="lr-stat__l">of buyers say peer conversations are among the most influential factors in their purchase decisions.</div></div>
        <div class="lr-stat w-reveal w-reveal--scale"><div class="lr-stat__n">37%</div><div class="lr-stat__l">of proof-seeking happens off your channels — much of it beyond what your team can see.</div></div>
        <div class="lr-stat w-reveal w-reveal--scale"><div class="lr-stat__n">79%</div><div class="lr-stat__l">of the time, the buyer is the one who starts the proof-seeking.</div></div>
      </div>
      <p class="lr-src w-reveal">GTM 2026 Benchmark Survey, Heinz Marketing + SlashExperts.</p>
      <p class="lr-bridge w-reveal">Here's the part most teams miss: you're not short on proof. You already have customers who've done the exact thing this buyer is weighing. The hard part is getting the right one's word in front of the right buyer while the decision is still live — reliably, and at scale. That's the job a Trust Layer exists to do.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="lr-stack">
  <section class="lr-proof" data-nav-surface="dark" aria-label="A peer conversation">
    <div class="lr-proof__bg" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="w-container">
      <div class="lr-proof__inner w-reveal">
        <p class="lr-proof__q">"The one voice with nothing to gain — another customer who's already done it."</p>
        <p class="lr-proof__c">Every real conversation between a buyer and a customer who's been in their seat is a proof point your competitors can't fabricate. A Trust Layer's whole job is to make that conversation happen on purpose, not by luck.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
